Listing highlights

Peace and quiet

This home is in a quiet area.

At-home coffee

Start your morning right with the french press and espresso machine.

Furry friends welcome

Bring your pets along for the stay.
Minimal studio apartment in a lush garden on a small hill in the outskirts of the village. Suitable for those who seek peace and quite, except for the occasional deer intruder, some cat ruckus which comes and goes as they are, and the rhythmic hoot of a friend owl. Ideal for those who love flowers and trees, starlit nights, and if lucky, a magnificent full moon view from the premises.

The space
The studio provides a double-sized bed, a compact chest drawer and a hanger. A small yet decent table with two chairs can accommodate your breakfast, lunch and dinner, which you will be able to provide your self, if you feel like it, since the kitchen area is fully equipped. If you really don't have a mood for it, the village is famous for its cuisine, and it is highly recommended to grab a bite anywhere you feel like. The bathroom has it all - except bubble baths, but a shower will do just fine.

All wonderful! The studio is exactly as described and well-equipped, a lovely place to stay if you're looking for a bit of peace and quiet to start/end your days in Rhodes. We will really miss the adorable Aris and the cats of the garden, very very happy to have found this place that felt like home this past week 🌞

We had a wonderful stay in the little house. The kitchen is perfectly equipped, and the local tea was delicious. Bonus: The friendly dog Aris greeted us every day - he’s just incredibly cute. Psinthos is a charming village! Tip: try the restaurant Smaragd!
